  "texts": [
    "For example, A female and a male candidate with similar qualifications should have equal chances of being approved for a job interview.",
    "• Causal probabilistic logic: Scholars explore causal probabilistic logic to remove the ambiguity of the judgment-based causal fairness idea.",
    "Causal probabilistic logic is a type of logic that attempts to understand the relationships between cause and effect in probabilistic terms.",
    "One crucial aspect of causal probabilistic logic is the use of counterfactuals, which are statements about what would have happened if a particular event had not occurred.",
    "Counterfactuals allow one to reason about the causal effects of interventions and can be used to test causal hypotheses [50]."
  ]
}